 notice them or that there isn't any.Only ""bad"" thing about this game is that it's LONG and I mean LOOOOONG. It took me a WEEK (probably longer, I can't remember) to read the damn thing (I can't remember clearly but I think I read atleast 4-8 hours a day, give or take some breaks doing something else) and during that week, I felt like I was in HIIIIGH heaven. Probably exaggeration but one thing is for sure, this visual novel will break your mind.For me, a visual novel being long is a good thing if the reading is exciting and captivating. For some people it's bad a thing, they probably want to do something else than spend whole day reading a book you cannot stop reading. This visual novel is one of the rare visual novel's that keep surprising you with ""It didn't end here? It's still going on? HELL YEAH"" and when you're finally at the end you feel drained and depressed that the thing you've read has ended.So to close this all up.Make absolutely sure not to spoil yourself about this game and prepare a LOT of time to read this, preferable alone at some summer cottage during weekends in middle of nowhere where noone can disturb you."
