,Recommended,449840,35059474,Posted: 19 September,all,isuyou,"When I first read Muv-Luv Alternative a few years back, I wasn’t sure what to expect. Coming off of Extra/Unliminted (the prequels), the series didn’t seem to have gotten off to a good start. But after indulging in it for nearly 100 hours over 2 weeks, I was so engaged in this visual novel that I can firmly say that it is my favorite of all time.Alternative completely deviates from the atmosphere and tone set in Extra/Unlimited and takes a more serious, gritty approach to sci-fi worlds. It takes the characters established in Extra and the setting introduced in Unlimited, then pushed them to their maximum potential.Muv Luv Alternative is an epic in the full sense of the word. It is a long journey that takes you and the characters through many trials and tribulations. This novel manages to fill every crossroad with meaning and growth. It invests so much into its characters to make every loss painful and every victory as heartfelt as possible.I have no good way to relay all the emotions and respect I have for this title. Alternative is truly one of the best sequels to exist being much better Extra/Unlimited. In fact, I’d even go venture to say that it is one of the best sci-fi adventures I have ever read. But more than that, the story has left such a great impression on me that I can’t forget any of the moments in it. I became so invested into the world and the characters struggling through it. Everything they felt, I felt as well.Of course, Muv Luv Alternative is not without its flaws, but I’ll let other reviews sift through those fine points. It’s not something for the faint of heart as for how dark and gruesome it can get. But, I wanted to share a bit of my own feelings and experiences with this work to hopefully inspire others to witness this masterpiece. Muv Luv Alternative is an experience like no other, and as such, I highly recommend it to anyone with even the slightest bit of interest. ."
76561198077098317,Recommended,449840,35059674,Posted: 19 September,all,Alternative IV,"An experience quite unlike any other.Never have I been so emotionally manipulated by any other sort of media. When things began turning for the worse I had a difficult time coping with and accepting what was happening.It's not a perfect story by any means. It has some pacing issues, a ton of exposition at certain points and personally while the main character's development is exceptional some of his irritating personality traits from the original persist throughout the novel. Yet, if there was any experience in any media I could convey to others, Alternative would be it.Possibly both Alternative's biggest boon and sin is the necessity of its predecessor. While the original Muv Luv had many cringe-worthy absurdities the player had to trek through, it was imperative to really see what the main character is fighting for and how that influences the actions he takes, along with how the world affects him. Above all I feel, is that it really helps immerse the player into the MC's role and mindset. This particular element is what makes some of Alternative's best and infamous scenes so emotionally compelling. I have never been sent into such a state of disarray by one certain scene and most people who have read MLA will know what scene I'm referring to.The writer supposedly sold his ancestral home to fund this game(which originally released in 2006) and it really shows with the production values far exceeding that of most modern VNs. The in-game sprites are all lip-synced and blink, the sound-design is top notch, there's a dedicated UI for when you're in a mech, a ridiculous amount of CGs, a ton of sprites including minor characters and a ton of sprite animations for both the characters and mechs.If anyone has any shred of interest in this, I implore them to go in as blind as possible. I wish the in-game menus and promotional material didn't spoil a bunch of elements but even so I can whole-heartedly recommend this. I can't guarantee it'll be your favorite VN or anything(there are many who would refer to Alternative as such) it's something that will certainly stand out among its peers and present you with an experience only it can offer."
