,Recommended,449840,35199457,Posted: 25 September,all,Mori Summer,"I have now played through this visual novel 3 times, and I still manage to laugh and cry as much as the first time I read it. The story covers so many different topics that I don't think it's possible to really put it into a genre. As much as people will tell you that you need to read the first ones, I've already lost so many potential readers to the monotony of the first two games. But as almost every person that has gone through the journey of the three games will tell you, the payoff is insanely worth it. It's got more action, strategic tension, and plot twists than Code Geass. The characters and the world that you're thrust into contain personality, grit, and lore that simply can't be found in anime with time and dialogue constraints. But the visual novel also never forgets to make you laugh and make connections with the people struggling with you. At the risk of sounding like a complete tool, I think Muv Luv Alternative has the best story that any Japanese medium has to offer.The new translation is an improvement off the fan translation overall, and many of the physics concepts that are explained throughout the novel are easier to understand as a result. Sex scenes still exist in this version, with the images zoomed in and edited to avoid showing any nudity. I do not imagine that this will impact the experience of many readers. Only the most explicit of dialogue is cut, and Sekai Project clearly made an effort to stay faithful to the original as much as possible with the limitations of Steam. Also, English vocals are thankfully much improved from the original. As such, I don't think it's necessary to go through the trouble of patching the game to 18+.The production values on this visual novel are incredible in some aspects, and mediocre in others. Many people do not like the art style of the characters, but the animation quality of the action sequences and the broad set of facial expressions that come with the art style more than make up for it for me.I'm going to be one of the dissenting opinions and tell you that if you have a history of dropping shows after the first few episodes bore you, then maybe you should just skip straight to Muv-Luv Unlimited. This will severely degrade the experience, but even this degraded experience is amazing by itself, and most of the foreshadowing and flashbacks in Alternative refer to Muv-Luv Unlimited. Though Muv-Luv Extra and Unlimited combined are shorter than Alternative, this doesn't change the fact that Extra by itself can take 15-20 hours of your time, and is notoriously generic and boring for those seeking a strong story and tension.I'm bad at conclusions."
