76561197989773636,Recommended,449840,35087733,Posted: 20 September,all,sporked,"Personal bias disclaimer: I own every MuvLuv related visual novel prior to Total Eclipse including Chronicles, Haruko Maniax etc.The conclusion to what is basically the longest single sci-fi visual novel written with Extra and Unlimited basically being both an extremely long prologue and world building chapters. Alternative builds on everything introduced in the two previous installments and then dials it up to eleven. All the character building, all the world building, all those odd little moments that sort of didn't make sense in the context they were presented, ALL of it is relevant so if you enjoyed those aspects and they piqued your interest then you are going to love Alternative.This version is also far more polished than the fan translated version. While the translation was good in the fan version, it felt a little sterile and didn't quite capture each characters various methods of speech, especially Tsukuyomi, Meiya and Takeru. The images were also only partially translated but that was mostly down to the limitations of the tools used to extract and modify the images, seeing them fully translated though really makes a difference. This version also includes more voice lines for Takeru and additional scenes that weren't included in the initial PC release (I believe this is a port of MuvLuv Alternative Winows 7 edition) so even for people like myself who have read it several times and have seen every 'ending' theres still new things to see.All in all an excellently done localisation of the single best sci-fi visual novel ever written, quite possibly THE  best visual novel full stop."
