,Recommended,449840,35121424,Posted: 21 September,all,Viper Zero,"No review i give can do it justice but here it is anyway.""A destiny tossed about, in an insane world---A flame of life blazing forth, in a dying world---And now, one more future that is spun---This is the alternative ending unable to be told before:A very great, a very tiny, a very precious...Tale of love and courage.""Muv-Luv Alternative continues the story of Shirogane Takeru after the events of the original Muv-Luv. This is a tale of a love so deep it breaks all barriers; about courage in the face of adversity and overcoming hardships. Takeru encounters and conquers insurmountable odds while his entire world is turned upside down around him.-Description onVNDB.orgThis is considered by one of the greatest pieces of storytelling i have ever read.The story will bombard you with a barrage of emotions, from happiness to disgust, from sadness to ""get away from her you ♥♥♥♥♥.""Now as i have made it clear in my previous review for Muv-Luv, READ THE ORIGINAL MUV-LUV FIRST. It is imperative that you do so. Not only does it foreshadow a lot of things but it is best to get all the main characters fleshed out. Now thats out of the way, lets go.Pros-Epic soundtrack.-Mecha action.-Political conspiracies lurking in the shadows.-Loveable characters.-Nearly all characters, even the very minor side ones can bring you to tears.-Replayability-Does not shy away to truly let you know how horrifying this was against the BETA is.Cons-Some scenes can feel oddly paced, especially an intense battle scene where the characters say a lot of things when in reality they would've died from how fast the enemy is halfway through their sentence.Verdict : 991/10"
